he same information exists for Smartphone SDK and CabWiz for Smartphone\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 . For more information, please consult the Smartphone SDK. }{\fs20\insrsid15337791 
\par 
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\tx450\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\fs20\insrsid15337791 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 1.  Application Installation (AppInstall) Overview
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 -\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 -----------------------------------------------------------------
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 1.1.\tab What is AppInstall?
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Application Installation (AppInstall) is the mechanism used to install }{\fs20\insrsid7233056 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Pocket PC}{\fs20\insrsid15337791 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  applications to a }{\fs20\insrsid7233056 
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Pocket PC}{\fs20\insrsid15337791 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  device.  AppInstall supports multi\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
ple installation methods, such as desktop-to-device, web-to-device, Storage Card-to-device, and device-to-device.
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 It is comprised of }{\fs20\insrsid479777 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 4}{\fs20\insrsid15337791 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  tools - CAB Wizard (CabWiz), }{\fs20\insrsid479777 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 CAB Wizard }{
\fs20\insrsid7233056 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 for Smartphone (CabWiz}{\fs20\insrsid479777 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 SP), }{\fs20\insrsid15337791 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Applic\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
ation Manager (AppMgr), and WCELoad.  CAB Wizard is the desktop SDK tool that packages your application binaries into a single }{\fs20\insrsid7233056 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Pocket PC}{\fs20\insrsid15337791 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
 CAB file.  Application Manager is the desktop ActiveSync component that provides the user a desktop-to-device\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  application management tool.  WCELoad is the }{\fs20\insrsid7233056 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Pocket PC}{
\fs20\insrsid15337791 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  tool that unpacks a }{\fs20\insrsid7233056 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Pocket PC}{\fs20\insrsid15337791 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  CAB file to install your application to the device.
\par 
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 1.2.\tab Where can I get it?
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 CAB Wizard is used by the application creator, and is part of the }{\fs20\insrsid7233056 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Pocket PC}{\fs20\insrsid15337791 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
 SDK.  Application Manager is used by both the application creator and the end-user, and is included with every installation of ActiveSync.  WCELoad is used by the end-user, and is included with most }{\fs20\insrsid7233056 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
Pocket PC}{\fs20\insrsid15337791 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  devices.
\par 
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 1.3.\tab Where\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  is the documentation?
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 The Application Installation documentation is part of the }{\fs20\insrsid7233056 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Pocket PC}{\fs20\insrsid15337791 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
 SDK Programmer's Guide, under the Connection Services section.  This documentation includes the input file to CabWiz (the CabWiz INF file), the input file\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  to AppMgr (the AppMgr INI file), as well as samples of both files.

\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Also, the input to CAB Wizard (the CabWiz INF file) uses a modified Win32 INF file format.  The Win32 INF file format is documented in the Win32 Platform SDK documentation, under the Setu\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
p API section.
\par 
\par 
